Comment (src/views/system/OverviewView.vue:432):
**[medium] Dead code: `systemImplementationStats` is never rendered — this null-safe fix patches a loader with no observable output.**

The `systemImplementationStats` ref is not referenced anywhere in the template (neither here nor on `main` — only the script declaration and this assignment exist). Yet every Overview mount fires 4 API calls (`users`, `components`, `inventory-items`, `leveraged-authorizations`) solely to populate it.

Rather than null-proofing dead code, remove the whole block: the `systemImplementationStats` ref, the four `executeSI*` `useDataApi` handles, this `Promise.allSettled` block, and the catch/`console.warn`. That eliminates the console-noise source entirely (better than guarding it) and saves 4 HTTP requests per Overview visit. The spec's "preserve all displayed values" is not in tension — these values were never displayed. The new test in `systemViews.spec.ts` ("loads overview implementation statistics from null lists without warning") would go with it.
