Comment (src/views/system/DiagramsView.vue:305):
**[low] Phantom seeded diagram still reachable on non-404 failures.**

This 404 reset correctly fixes the missing-group case, but `authorizationBoundary` is still seeded with `initialData: { diagrams: [{ uuid: v4() }] }` (line 211, unlike the other two groups which seed `{}`). Two paths still render that phantom never-created diagram — a blank editor whose Save/Delete target a UUID the API never issued:

1. A non-404 fetch failure (500, network error) — the rethrow here leaves the seeded initialData in place.
2. A 200 response with a null payload — `useDataApi`'s data watcher does `val?.data ?? initialData`, falling back to the seeded blank diagram.

Suggest changing the authorization-boundary `initialData` to `{} as Diagrammable` to match `networkArchitecture`/`dataFlow`. The empty-state markup (`v-if="authorizationBoundary?.diagrams?.length"` / `v-else`) already handles it, and no failure path can then show a phantom editor.
