Comment (src/views/system/UsersView.vue:168):
**[low] Empty state affirmatively claims "No users defined" when the fetch fails.**

If `fetchUsers()` rejects, the rejection escapes `onMounted` unhandled, `usersLoading` settles to `false`, and `users` stays `undefined` — so this computed turns true and the view invites "Create your first user to get started" with no error surfaced. Before this change the failure mode was a blank area (bad, but not misleading).

ComponentsView in this same PR handles it properly (catch + error toast + explicit `[]`). Suggest either including the error ref in the gate — `const { data, isLoading, error, execute } = useDataApi(...)` and `!error.value &&` here — or mirroring ComponentsView's catch-and-toast in `loadData`.
